  "helpButtonTooltip": "Help — what is this section?",
  "helpSocialTitle": "Social",
  "helpSocialBody": "Stay in touch with the community. Browse the Feed for posts and game listings, message other players, and apply to open tables. Community content lives on a separate Marketplace sub-tab.",
  "helpSettingsTitle": "Settings",
  "helpSettingsBody": "Configure your account, theme, language, projection display and cloud sync. Sign-in and profile management live here too.",
  "helpWorldsTitle": "Worlds",
  "helpWorldsBody": "A world is where your game lives — characters, NPCs, items, spells, maps, mind map, session notes and rules all sit under one roof. Each world is a fully self-contained campaign with its own database, sessions and media. You can start one of two ways: download a ready-made world skeleton and layer your own characters and NPCs on top, or design everything from scratch and build an original game. Nothing is locked down on the Worlds side — the structure, rules and content are yours to shape. Click a world card to open it; the gear icon on the card handles rename, delete, share and publish.",
  "helpTemplatesTitle": "Templates",
  "helpTemplatesBody": "Templates define the bare bones of a game — which field types exist, which default entities ship with it, how rules behave. Their goal is twofold: to put different settings (fantasy, sci-fi, horror, modern, …) in front of players, and to give everyone a way to design and share their own custom setting. From a template you can spin up new worlds with a single click, roll your own template from scratch, or pull down templates other players have designed on the Marketplace. Templates publish to the Marketplace as immutable snapshots, so the version you share with the community stays intact over time.",
  "helpPackagesTitle": "Packages",
  "helpPackagesBody": "Packages are ready-made content cards you drop directly onto a setting or template. Think of a pre-built spell pack, a healing-herbs pack, a monster list, a loot set or a bundle of mind-map nodes — you import it into the active world in one go and start using it right away. Packages are the fastest way to move content between worlds and to share it: export your own pack and bring it into another world, or publish it to the Marketplace for the community. Importing happens from the Packages tab, and imported content behaves indistinguishably from the world's native content.",
  "helpMarketplaceTitle": "Marketplace",
  "helpMarketplaceBody": "The Marketplace is a free platform where players share the content they create. Worlds, templates and packages are all published here — anyone can download them, add them to their own game and build on top. Every publish is stored as an immutable snapshot: once live, it cannot be edited, only deleted, so the version in a downloader's hands never drifts underneath them. To publish your own content, open the Marketplace panel in the settings of the world, template or package you want to share. To browse, head to the Marketplace sub-tab under Social.",

